1
00:00:04,567 --> 00:00:07,917
If you have ever taken care of plants
you know that they need to be

2
00:00:08,135 --> 00:00:11,910
watered so that they don't welt.
That's because plants take water up

3
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:16,074
into their cells and this water
pressure helps keep them upright.

4
00:00:16,316 --> 00:00:19,741
But have you ever seen on a really
hot day, plants welting

5
00:00:19,956 --> 00:00:22,256
even though they appear
to have enough water?

6
00:00:22,891 --> 00:00:26,391
That's because a plant's respiration
includes transpiration

7
00:00:26,599 --> 00:00:31,311
of moisture out of their leaves.
On a hot day this transpiration

8
00:00:31,523 --> 00:00:34,598
can occur faster than plants can
take up more water

9
00:00:34,811 --> 00:00:38,961
causing them to welt even when
they do have access to water.

10
00:00:39,562 --> 00:00:42,449
Following this module you
will be able to explain

11
00:00:42,665 --> 00:00:46,278
treatments processes and operation
of planted drying beds,

12
